{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"88e1b602-a252-4a4e-b4e8-d55afe25020d","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped/ignored** (not failed) in test results, with your reason visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c5a46cd1-2853-4e16-bd97-4f5b119acd55","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":306,"requestId":"67C8:163FFF:1666FE2:19336D7:69FD3A52"},"id":"28e4c8a0-8668-408f-975c-c7d0bff562b4","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:20:25.232Z","parentId":"0010e3b9-031b-467a-a7a4-98df441db31b"}
